
# LEAP CAN – Application Engineering Support Scope
## Detailed Service Breakdown for Commercial Support Allocation

**Document status:** Working Draft  
**Scope focus:** Application Engineering Support  
**Program:** LEAP – CAN Integration  
**Reference platform:** LEAP Investment production implementation  

---

> ## Purpose
>
> This document defines the detailed scope of the **Application Engineering Support** service required to integrate the CAN workstream into the LEAP production platform established by the Investment implementation.
>
> The commercial allocation between **Infrastructure Support** and **Application Support** will be confirmed separately. This document focuses exclusively on the **Application Support** portion and describes the activities, execution model, responsibilities, deliverables and expected outcomes associated with that service.

> ## Important Scope Boundary
>
> This service is not limited to incident resolution or operational support. It provides specialized application engineering support across architecture, security, frontend, backend, orchestration, integration, testing, release readiness and production stabilization.
>
> Infrastructure ownership, networking, landing zone, cloud account configuration and platform-level operational activities remain subject to validation by the Infrastructure and DevOps leads.

---

# 1. Service Objective

The Application Engineering Support service provides specialized technical guidance and hands-on support to safely integrate CAN application components into an existing production platform.

The service is intended to:

- Protect the stability of the Investment production implementation.
- Reduce integration and release risk.
- Validate that CAN application components follow the established LEAP engineering model.
- Support the integration of frontend, backend, APIs, Lambda functions and Step Functions.
- Ensure application-level security, observability, testing and operational readiness.
- Support controlled production releases and post-release stabilization.
- Transfer platform-specific knowledge to the CAN delivery team.

---

# 2. Business and Technical Context

The CAN delivery team is developing application capabilities that will later be incorporated into the LEAP platform.

At the time of integration:

- Investment will already be deployed and operating in production.
- Shared application services, cloud patterns and deployment mechanisms will already exist.
- CAN will introduce new screens, backend services, workflow orchestration and system integrations.
- The integration will require controlled changes to application code, shared components and release artifacts.
- The application integration must avoid regressions or disruption to the Investment production workload.
- Application components must align with the architecture, security, testing and operational standards established by the reference implementation.

This creates a higher level of complexity than an isolated or greenfield application deployment.

---

# 3. Application Support Operating Model

The Application Engineering Support team acts as a multidisciplinary SME function covering the following domains:

| Domain | Primary Focus |
|---|---|
| Application Architecture | Solution integrity, component boundaries, integration patterns and technical decisions |
| Application Security | Secure coding, authorization, sensitive data handling and vulnerability remediation |
| Frontend Engineering | Screen integration, frontend-backend contracts, navigation and error handling |
| Backend Engineering | APIs, business services, Lambda functions, shared libraries and integrations |
| Workflow Orchestration | Step Functions, screen orchestration, state management, retries and exception flows |
| Quality Engineering | Test strategy, integration validation, regression coverage and release evidence |
| Observability | Application logs, metrics, traces, alarms and production diagnostics |
| Release Support | Production readiness, release validation, rollback and hypercare |

