## 4.2 Specification and Functional Flow Review

### Objective

Ensure that CAN business flows are sufficiently defined before application integration and development changes are introduced.

### Activities

- Review available business flows and process documentation.
- Validate screen sequencing and user navigation.
- Validate functional rules and decision points.
- Validate input and output data for each screen.
- Validate user actions and expected system responses.
- Validate alternate, exception and rejection flows.
- Validate timeout, retry and cancellation scenarios.
- Validate dependencies on external systems.
- Validate API requirements for each functional step.
- Validate state transitions across the end-to-end journey.
- Validate frontend, backend and orchestration responsibilities.
- Review acceptance criteria.
- Identify missing or ambiguous requirements.
- Confirm traceability between process, specification, implementation and tests.
- Support the refinement of functional and technical specifications.
- Validate that application changes are versioned and approved.

### Execution Approach

The support team conducts specification review sessions using the CAN journey, screen flows, API contracts and orchestration requirements as the baseline.

### Deliverables

- Specification Review Report.
- Functional Flow Findings.
- Requirements Clarification Log.
- Traceability Matrix.
- Updated Acceptance Criteria.
- Technical Decision Log.

### Completion Criteria

- Critical business flows are fully mapped.
- Application behavior is defined for happy path and exception scenarios.
- Technical implementation can be traced to approved specifications.

